  "text": "According to [CITATION_1] , satisfaction is partially determined by policies and supervision and a firm's ethical climate are affected by both of them. The top management decides the policies depending on what they view as appropriate or inappropriate behavior. Regardless, managers like leaders play a major role in determining the organization's ethical climate and play a significant role in affecting employee's ethical behavior (Ferrel and Gresham, 1985) . Therefore, the ethical climate is formed by management and becomes an important force driving not only ethical behavior but also job-related outcomes.",
